One of the most captivating moments of the 2nd BSCF Astronomy Camp 2025 was the astrophotography session conducted by Zubuyer Kaolin, a passionate astro photographer and science communicator. Through an impressive collection of night sky photographs captured from different parts of Bangladesh, he brought the universe closer to the audience. Participants were fascinated by the stories behind each image, learning about the patience, dedication, and creativity involved in capturing the cosmos. His presentation transformed astronomy into a blend of science, art, and imagination, making complex ideas accessible and engaging. The hall was filled with awe, curiosity, laughter, and inspiration throughout the session. This experience encouraged participants to see the night sky not only as a subject of scientific study but also as a source of creativity and wonder, truly reflecting a journey through the lens where stars met stories.
